
businesses needs money. They give out "bonds". You buy bonds, they get the money, and they promise you to pay you an interest, this case called a "coupon". So this is kind of a loan from the business.

Bonds differ from stocks. "Stocks represent partial ownership in a company, and the returns represent a share in profits"

Government bonds (US-specific):
- < 1yr: T-bills
- 1yr << 10yr: T-notes
- > 10yr: treasury bonds
Municipal bonds
